All is now set for Chelsea Football Club to sign Barcelona’s forward, Ousmane Dembele, Sky Sports reports. This is after Paris Saint-Germain pulled out of the deal to sign the French forward. The French champions have now decided to bolster their midfield and not attack, allowing Thomas Tuchel’s side to move ahead to sign the player. Thomas Tuchel had once described the French star as “one of the craziest talents” he has ever seen. The German coach had previously worked with Dembele at Borrusia Dortmund The France World Cup winner joined Barcelona from Dortmund for a record £125million fee in 2017. Since his arrival, he has made 150 appearances for the club where he has scored 32 goals and assisted 34.